violence has to feel right, as a collective, for an organisation and its followers to move from moderate activism to (violent) extremism. She shows that organisations mediate this change by performing collective emotions in and through narrative. The book offers a provocative and nuanced account which departs from conventional interpretations of radicalisation and reminds us of the power of emotions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Violence in Society.2bisacsh1 aClément, Maéva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526167705zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526167705zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526167705/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-MUPb2023